# WORKSPACES

## `workspaces`

`path` (ltree) permite validar profundidad en O(1) y queries de subtree eficientes.
`parent_workspace_id` se mantiene como referencia de integridad relacional.

| Campo | Tipo | Notas |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | bigint | |
| `name` | string | |
| `owner_user_id` | FK → users.id | |
| `parent_workspace_id` | FK → workspaces.id nullable | null = raíz |
| `path` | ltree | ej: `"1.5.23.47"` — índice GiST requerido |
| `status` | enum | `active`, `archived`, `orphaned` |
| `created_at` | timestamp | |
| `updated_at` | timestamp | |
| `deleted_at` | timestamp nullable | |

**Índice requerido:**
```sql
CREATE INDEX workspaces_path_gist ON workspaces USING GIST (path);
```

**Validación de profundidad antes de insertar:**
```sql
-- nlevel('1.5.23') = 3
SELECT nlevel(path) + 1 <= plan.max_workspace_depth FROM workspaces WHERE id = :parent_id
```

